

# This file contains all stars brighter than visual magnitude (m_V) of 2.5.

# Common papers:
#   The names of these papers are not folded in order to make searching for them easier.

# Baines et al. (2021), AJ 162 (5), id.198
#   "Angular Diameters and Fundamental Parameters of Forty-four Stars from the Navy Precision Optical Interferometer"
#   https://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.3847/1538-3881/ac2431
#   https://scixplorer.org/abs/2021AJ....162..198B/abstract

# Baines et al. (2025), AJ 169 (6), id.293
#   "Vintage NPOI: New and Updated Angular Diameters for 145 Stars"
#   https://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.3847/1538-3881/adc930
#   https://scixplorer.org/abs/2025AJ....169..293B/abstract

# Che et al. (2011), ApJ 732 (2), 68
#   "Colder and Hotter: Interferometric Imaging of β Cassiopeiae and α Leonis"
#   https://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.1088/0004-637X/732/2/68
#   https://scixplorer.org/abs/2011ApJ...732...68C/abstract

# Lazzarotto et al. (2026)
#   "Fundamental properties of two rapidly rotating stars: Rasalhague and Alkaid"
#   https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.11189



# BRIGHTEST STARS (m_V <= 2.5)
